    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is offset by the high relevance of the validation scenario and the conservative acceptance bounds applied. The overall credibility evidence, drawn from a comprehensive literature survey of analogous pedicle screw FEA studies and cross-referenced against published benchmark ranges, supports acceptance of the FEA model for the stated COU. The assessment team concludes that the model is fit for purpose for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw compression-bending prediction.",
